Shape.name: The WP shall consider the ESA space ontology
Shape.Text: Since ESA is a customer / partner of the major involved COOPERANTS partners, it makes sense to address their use cases. COOPERANTS is be expected to be used in this context

Shape.name: The WP shall only consider the applications of Airbus and DLR
Shape.Text: Scope Limitation: We will only consider the use cases of the current 4.2.1 partners, driven by Airbus and DLR in order to have scope maangement

Shape.name: The WP shall not need to accept requirements for other applications than the ones discussed in the TVB
The WP shall emphasize an implementation that is license free / open source for the duration of the project
The WP shall exclude functionality that is only available in commercial versions of the used software (for the duration of the project), such as sharding, replication etc.
The WP may build mockups / alternatives for functionality availablity in the commercial versions of used software, but which is required for demonstration (e.g. authorization)
The WP SHALL choose a set of budget calculations for demonstration
Shape.Text: Show that budget calculation works for e.g. for mass / power, this implies other budgets will work, too

Shape.name: The system SHALL provide an API to raw data
The system SHALL provide an API to semantic data that follows the meta-model or onotology
The system SHALL store data that is structured (as in elements, relations, such as SysML / UML)
The system SHALL store elements that have properties (such as class instance descriptions)
The system SHALL allow access only to authorized users
The system SHALL support a configurable meta-model or ontology
The system SHALL validate the content of the repository according to a meta-model or ontology
The system SHALL support the definition of dynamic types / category
The system SHALL support the assignment of more than one class / category to modelled elements
The system SHALL support the setting of attribute values based on the dynamic class / categoy assignments
The system SHALL support reuse of parts of a model in a new derived model
The system MAY implement the partial reuse as a copy (no live update when source changes)
The system SHALL support the update of the reused model parts at the place where it is used
The system SHALL provide a standard internet accessible API
The system SHALL store data that is graph-based

If the system has elements with the same unique identifier in different scopes, the system SHALL consider these copies of the same element (although possibly in different versions)
The system SHALL support relationships based on the unique identifiers
The system SHALL support globally unique identifiers that are eternally unique
The system SHALL support retrieval of elements based on the unique identifiers
A scope is defined as the set of elements that can reference ("see") each other.

The system SHALL support copying of elements from one scope to another

The system SHALL keep the same unique id when copying objects from one scope to another
The system SHALL ensure uniqueness of unique identifiers within a scope

The system SHALL support an API for retrieval of all elements that are within another elements scope.
The system SHALL support the grouping of arbitrary data to a collection of data sets

The system MUST NOT consider data set inclusion as a type of containment

The system SHALL provide a mechanism for possibly including required related elements in a data set automatically
The system SHALL support write / change protection for data sets
The system SHALL provide queries based on relationships between elements.

The system SHALL support the derivation of data optimized for time series analysis

The system SHALL provide a mechanism for the integration of the concept of derived models into the concept of scopes and data sets

The system SHALL provide compare functionality for time series data
The system SHALL provide compare functionalty for element data

The system SHALL store various versions of an object
The system SHALL allow the update / change of the meta-model
The system SHALL support read access by more than one user
The system SHALL support editing / write access by more than one user at a time
The system SHALL detect conflicting changes when written by multiple users

The system SHALL support authentication based on GAIA-X standards

Shape.name: The ontology SHALL support specifying rules for the quality of data.
Shape.Text:
E.g.: some data item in the model. When does the data-item have enough maturity/reliability to be reliable for the next steps in the development process.
Quality criteria should be rules / etc. that are executed automatically.
